Construction and engineering company Group Five announced today that its interim CEO, Dr Thabo Clifford Kogo, has tendered his resignation, effective from 30 October, to pursue an alternative career opportunity. Koko was appointed in July 2017 as non-executive director and agreed to be Interim CEO from 1 February 2019, shortly before the company was placed into business rescue. Group Five’s statement said: “Subsequent to the approval of the business rescue plan for the company on 11
September 2019, the BRPs are now implementing the approved plan. As such, they don’t yet foresee appointing a replacement CEO. Group Five’s listing on the JSE will be terminated and the company wound up but between 3 000 and 3 500 jobs saved through the restructuring and sale of businesses and contracts to new owners